<recipe>
<title>
Slow Cooker Dr Pepper BBQ Chicken
</title>
<details>

</details>
<ingredients>
4-6 boneless skinless chicken breasts
1 lemon
1 yellow or white onion
20 ounce bottle of BBQ sauce*
12 ounce can of Dr Pepper**
</ingredients>
<instructions>
Peel onion and cut into quarters.
Cut lemon into quarters.
Place chicken breasts in crock pot.
Place onion and lemon quarters on top.
Pour in entire bottle of BBQ sauce and can of Dr. Pepper.
Cover and cook on low for 6-8 hours.
</instructions>
</recipe>
